HEADWORD: Mischaracterize
<hw>Mis*char"ac*ter*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
characterize falsely or erroneously; to give a wrong character
to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They totally <qex>mischaracterize</qex> the action.</q>
<rj><qau>Eton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

